rComments: Class was babyish.  Dr. Farner also is not someone to go to if you have a problem.  She has no maternal instincts whatsoever and she will make you feel worse.  She is good at working, that's all.

This class was absurdly easy, but incredibly dull. She is very nice and knows what shes teaching, but know that you are taking an intro to hospital management class. If you are not interested in the topic, it is probably not worth it.
Excellent teacher...If you want to see what all instructors should aspire to you should take a class with Dr. Farner.

this was a pretty interesting class. prof. Farner did a really good job of explaining the materials and gives out random points for going to class. tests are fairly easy because you're told whats gonna be tested. only problem was the room didnt have air conditioning so it was pretty easy to fall asleep

This is such an easy class. Farner is such a great professor and she's very caring. The class is very easy however, you do have to attend lecture because she gives random attendance points. Her exams are alittle tricky but if you study and read all the lecture notes you'll do extremely well. I though the class was an easy A

She's extremely smart! I love her comments and how she reads something of currents events in the beginning of class.  I'm up and never fell asleep in her class, unless of course you don't like Healthcare Sys subjects. Don't buy the book cuz everything you need is in her slides.
Easy A class but you can't skip bc you do hw at the end of every class to turn in. Tests are easy bc she gives you a studyguide that all the questions come off of.
A nice and easy class and she's a nice and caring lady
